rComments: Very boring lecturer, but he's there for you if you need help, and is decently approachable. The syllabus was no help, he told us on the first day that it was a "rough outline" and then changed the whole thing, every week. Labs are 3 hours and the lecture is right before, for 1.5,  so together it was a long 4.5 hour class. Hard to sit through

I don't know why everyone is complaining. Instructions are straight forward and he's very approachable.  His lectures are long but straight forward. People should realize the course could be much worse if it was offered by the engineering department, if it was we would have to learn the physics of remote sensing as well.

The prof was alright except the TAs that were supposed to explain the labs were not helpful at all. Instructions were also kind of muddy and I always had to go and ask for clarifications. Disappointed as I hoped to learn so much more in that class. Taught myself a lot since again, there was no proper instruction for the GIS software.

He is a very boring and monotone lecturer but he is very sweet and is always there to help if you need. The tests are super easy, so are the labs and for the final project the average was a 94% (the lowest grade was a 74% and that guy should have failed).
Dont skip. Need to learn the program.
